## Project structure

```text
├── configs/             # Version-controlled experiment and pipeline parameters
├── data/
│   ├── raw/             # Immutable source data
│   ├── interim/         # Intermediate transformed data
│   ├── processed/       # Model-ready datasets
│   └── external/        # Data from third parties
├── models/              # Serialized models (ignored by Git)
├── notebooks/           # Numbered exploration notebooks
├── reports/figures/     # Generated figures and reports
├── src/{{ project_name }}/    # Reusable project code
└── tests/               # Automated tests
```

## Setup

1. Install [uv](https://docs.astral.sh/uv/).
2. Run `uv sync`.
3. Copy `.env.example` to `.env` and add local secrets if needed.
4. Run `uv run jupyter lab` for notebooks.

## Development

```bash
uv run ruff check .
uv run ruff format .
uv run pytest
uv run {{ project_name | replace('_', '-') }}
```

Keep notebooks focused on exploration. Move reusable loading, feature, and modeling
logic into `src/{{ project_name }}/` and cover it with tests.
